details.address: 363 Church St N Suite 100, Concord, NC 28025
details.description: Welcome to The Perc at The Nook, a café where caffeine and comfort harmonize. Nestled within the enchanting Percent Beer, our second location invites you to indulge in expertly crafted lattes, aromatic coffee, and a symphony of teas. While savoring your preferred beverage, dive into our delectable light bites, designed to complement our invigorating drinks. Our inviting ambiance extends both indoors and out, with ample seating, reliable Wi-Fi, and convenient parking. At The Perc at The Nook, we create a cozy refuge for you to unwind, gather, and enjoy the convergence of coffee and community.

posts.body:
The Perc at The Nook is Now open!
Soft opening this week!
Hours: 7:00a - 3:00p daily.

reviews_data.review_text:
Such a nice laid back place in an easy spot to get in and out of. It’s never too busy. I ordered an iced matcha. The owner was super friendly and helpful. He made sure we all got our orders exactly as we wanted them.

The seating is very comfortable and good for any group size. We sat on a comfy couch.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Outdoor patio / terrace

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for the kind review! So happy you liked the matcha! 🙂

reviews_data.review_text: The food which was excellent was provided by a food truck out back. The staff was friendly and very helpful. The beer was very tasty as a nice, easy going atmosphere. I would highly recommend everybody try it

review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text: A beautiful environment with incredible service and great coffee! A must go-to to start the day!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you Eric!
So happy you liked our spot!
We appreciate you.

reviews_data.review_text: Spent an hour working from here. Loved the atmosphere! Great addition to the downtown Concord area!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Bettina! We appreciate you coming by and checking out our new spot!

reviews_data.review_text:
If you know me, you know I’m a coffee person. For years, I bounced around town looking for that perfect spot—someplace with a legit coffee selection, a welcoming atmosphere, and a little character. Well, I finally found it. This brand-new coffee shop is it.
The drink selection is incredible—something for every taste, from the classic espresso to creative seasonal specials. The staff? Super friendly, knowledgeable, and clearly passionate about what they do.
But what really sets this place apart is the vibe. The design is unique and thoughtful, with immaculate attention to detail. It’s got that “just opened” freshness, but already feels like your favorite local hangout.

Trust me—if you love great coffee and even better energy, you have to check it out.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much Jesse! We remember you! I believe you got something off the new Summer menu! We appreciate the honest and kind words. Next time you are in the area, please visit us!

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee, super cool space with a brewery and food truck incorporated, great service and treat options! I got a decaf latte and it was excellent. Very excited to have this new local coffee shop in our area.

review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! We appreciate the kind words! And we look forward to serving you!

reviews_data.review_text:
The best coffee! The cherry cordial is phenomenal and the owner is so kind. Good folks and coffee!

Thank you for the coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Emma! We appreciate the you stopping by the new location! Love the Cherry Cordial!
Thank you so much Winter!  You were our first customer and it melts our hearts that you liked our Snickerdoodle!
